title: The Making of a Nation: The Beginnings of Israel's History
creator: Charles Foster Kent
description: LibriVox recording of "The Making of a Nation: The Beginnings of Israel's History" by Charles Foster Kent; read by LibriVox volunteers, proofed by Karen Merline and produced by Kirsten Fererri. Charles Foster Kent was one of the premier scholars in Jewish Studies at the turn of the century. He was particularly well-known for his comparisons of early Christianity to its Jewish roots. He also wrote several distinguished histories of Israel, the Jewish people, Torah studies, and the development of oral Torah. (Summary by Kirsten Ferreri) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org Download M4B (142MB)
